-- Mauritania Grants Gold, Iron Ore, Copper Licenses, AMI Says
-- B y   O u d a a   M a r o u f
-- 2012-06-15T11:00:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-15/mauritania-grants-gold-iron-ore-copper-licenses-ami-says.html
Mauritania’s government granted
licenses to explore for gold to Orecorp Mauritania Sarl,  Drake
Resources Ltd. (DRK)  and MREM Sarl, state-owned Agence Mauritanienne
d’Information reported.  Exploration licenses for the precious metal were also given
to Mineralis Sarl, Maadin Sarl and SPIM Ressources Sarl, the
Nouakchott-based news agency said. Iron Ore permits were granted
to Mineralis Sarl, Nelvo International Minerals & Metals Sarl,
Negoce International Mining and SPIM Ressources Sarl, while a
quartz exploration license was awarded to Quartz Ing Mauritania
SA.  A copper license was granted to Mauri Mining SA, it said.  The decisions were made during the government’s weekly
Council of Ministers meeting, AMI reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Oudaa Marouf in Nouakchott at 
